Rating: 4
This tasted almost exactly like a dish I paid $12 for at a local restaurant. It was fantastic. As a guidenote, if you use Lite Coconut Milk, you'll want to add a little less lemon juice, or a little more oil, as the lack of cream turns the broth a little too acidic. And don't be afraid to put in as much curry powder as you like! 2 tbsp is fine, but I prefer about 3.

Rating: 4
impressive but easy. the most labor intensive part of this dish is debearding and cleaning the mussels. the sauce is light and flavorful. i wound up adding a little extra coconut milk, because the sauce seemed a bit too acidic with the wine and lemon. we served it over homemade lemon fettucini, and the flavors were divine. we experimented with wine pairings, and while both red and white worked with the dish, i think i preferred the pinot gris. the sauvignon blanc was a bit to bitter for the dish and the red--while it brought out the heat in the curry--mixed with the mussels to create a very sweet taste. super yummy. i wish i'd taken pictures.

